Interface MouseGraphAction

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MouseGraphEdge, MouseGraphNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MouseClickNode, MouseDragEdge, MouseHoverNode, MouseMoveEdge, MouseWindowNode

    public interface MouseGraphAction
    Represents an MouseEvent or group of MouseEvents in the browser window.
    Author:
    oalpha

    • Method Detail

      • getTimestamp

        long getTimestamp()
        Returns the timestamp of the MouseEvent or the earliest MouseEvent if this action represents multiple.
        Returns:
        the timestamp

      • getPrevious

        MouseGraphAction getPrevious()
        The action occurring immediately before this one. For MouseGraphEdges this is usually a MouseGraphNode and NouseGraphNodes this is usually a MouseGraphEdge. Exceptions include a user hovering before a click or executing a complicated movement that the GOD instance breaks up into multiple regressions.
        Returns:
        the previous action

      • getNext

        MouseGraphNode getNext()
        The action occurring immediately after this one.
        Returns:
        the next action

      • getError

        double getError()
        Returns how much the actual mouse data deviated from the regression. For edges, this the area between the actual path and the regression path. For nodes, this is the length of the actual path.
        Returns:
        the error

      • getVariance

        java.awt.geom.Dimension2D getVariance()
        Returns the variance of the actual path. For edges this is the variance of the velocity of the path and for nodes this is the variance of the position of the path.
        Returns:
        the variance

      • getRange

        java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D getRange()
        Returns the rectangular bounds of the path.
        Returns:
        the bounds

      • getArea

        java.awt.Shape getArea()
        Returns the shape of minimal area bounding the path.
        Returns:
        the bounds
